{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nGenerate `docs/cli-reference.md` from the CLI's OWN help data, so the command reference\ncannot drift, and gate it in CI like `scripts/gen_env_registry.py`.\n\n## Source of truth (verified — the CLI surface is two disjoint families)\n1. **50 help-backed subcommands** — fully enumerable, RELIABLE help text:\n   - `rebar._cli._help.known_subcommands() -> frozenset[str]` (returns 50).\n   - `rebar._cli._help.subcommand_help(sub) -> str|None` — the full pinned usage text\n     (package data under `rebar._cli.help/*.txt`). Reliable; use this for full help.\n2. **16 intercept-arm commands** — handled in `src/rebar/_cli/__init__.py` main() before the\n   `known_subcommands()` check (~lines 372-447), with NO `help/*.txt` and no overview row:\n   `reconcile, review, review-code, scan-spec, verify-completion, review-plan, sign-review,\n   enrich, explain, verify-commit-ticket, workflow, llm, jira-onboard, prompt, criteria,\n   config`.\n\n**Do NOT subprocess-capture `rebar <cmd> --help` for the intercepts.** Verified gotcha:\n`rebar enrich --help` has no argparse parser (`cmd_enrich()` in `rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py`)\n— it calls `drain()` and prints JSON with exit 0, so a \"non-empty + exit 0\" guard would\nsilently store JSON garbage as \"help\". Subprocess capture across 16 heterogeneous commands\nis fragile. Instead: carry a hardcoded **curated one-line description** for each of the 16\nintercept commands in the generator (`INTERCEPT_COMMANDS: dict[str,str]`), and DRIFT-GATE\nthe dict's key set against the `if argv[0] == \"...\"` ladder in `_cli/__init__.py` so a\nnewly-added intercept without a curated entry fails the generator loudly.\n\nTotal ~66 commands, all listed; the 50 with full pinned help, the 16 with a curated\none-liner (marked as advanced/intercept commands, \"see `rebar <cmd> --help`\").\n\n## Scope\n- Add `scripts/gen_cli_reference.py` (new): Family 1 via `_help.known_subcommands()` +\n  `subcommand_help()`; Family 2 via the `INTERCEPT_COMMANDS` curated dict. Emit\n  `docs/cli-reference.md` with a \"Generated by … do not edit\" header (mirror\n  `gen_env_registry.py`), each command name rendered backtick-wrapped for exact matching.\n- The generator asserts `set(INTERCEPT_COMMANDS) == <ladder set parsed from _cli/__init__.py>`\n  and exits non-zero on mismatch (so a new/removed intercept is caught — no subprocess).\n- `--check` mode: regenerate in memory, exit non-zero if committed file differs.\n- Wire a drift gate into BOTH `.github/workflows/test.yml` AND\n  `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` (the actual Verified gate; a parity test\n  `tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py` ENFORCES every `scripts/*.py` in test.yml also\n  appears in gerrit-verify.yaml — omitting the latter breaks `make test`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/cli-reference.md` is generated (marked generated) and lists BOTH families:\n      every `known_subcommands()` entry (50) with its full help AND all 16 intercept\n      commands with a curated one-liner.\n- [ ] Completeness proof, EXACT backtick match (no substring false positives like\n      `review` vs `review-plan`), prints nothing:\n      `python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py && for c in $(python -c \"from rebar._cli import _help; print(' '.join(sorted(_help.known_subcommands())))\") reconcile review review-code scan-spec verify-completion review-plan sign-review enrich explain verify-commit-ticket workflow llm jira-onboard prompt criteria config; do grep -qF \"\\`$c\\`\" docs/cli-reference.md || echo \"MISSING $c\"; done`\n- [ ] Intercept-drift guard: `set(INTERCEPT_COMMANDS)` equals the ladder set parsed from\n      `_cli/__init__.py`; a mismatch makes the generator exit non-zero. DETERMINISTIC proof\n      (prints `CAUGHT`): temporarily remove one key from the dict in memory and confirm the\n      generator's self-check fails — covered by a held-out unit test that mutates the dict\n      and asserts a non-zero/raise. (The generator runs this parity check on every run.)\n- [ ] Drift gate works — a stale committed reference fails `--check` (prints `CAUGHT`):\n      `python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py; printf '\\nstale\\n' >> docs/cli-reference.md; python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py --check >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo MISS || echo CAUGHT; python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py`\n- [ ] The gate is wired in BOTH CI files (prints nothing):\n      `for f in .github/workflows/test.yml .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml; do grep -qF 'gen_cli_reference.py' \"$f\" || echo \"NOT WIRED: $f\"; done`\n      and `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py -q` passes.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` stay green.\n\nFiles: `scripts/gen_cli_reference.py` (new), `docs/cli-reference.md` (new/generated),\n`.github/workflows/test.yml`, `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783826320391557001,"uuid":"f08054c5-bc08-478d-8ba9-220524a57cdf"}